Product Name: Carl Buddig
Arctic Glacier
Description: It may seem as easy as just freezing water but in fact ice exists at different purity levels. Arctic Glaciers filtration process takes regular city water and transforms it into bottled water quality purified water. The water is initially filtered through carbon filters and is then processed through water softeners. As water is the only ingredient to make ice, the quality should be monitored just like any other food product. At Arctic Glacier, this process is conducted on a weekly basis instead of monthly or even annually as usually.
